data.description: This comfortable 3 bedroom/2 bathroom home in Old Lely offers expansive golf course views, on a park-like, easy care, landscaped lot!  A timed well water irrigation system.”    Former owner, a contributing founder of Naples Botanical Gardens, designed and landscaped the property with trees, including a gorgeous Kapok, that overshadows a butterfly garden.    This home offers beautiful sunrises, sunsetting skies, and evening stars can be seen from your backyard.  This beachy cottage includes travertine floors throughout the wide open living area, allowing for ease of entertainment.  Cherry shaker cabinets in the kitchen, matching the bookshelf/display cabinets in the living room.  Beds/baths have tiled floors with updated fixtures.  Home includes a thirty (30) year GAF architectural roof installed in 2014 with a 21 year remaining lifespan.  The tankless water heater, electric panel, AC/handler, central vacuum, and ductwork have all been recently updated.  Homeowner is reinstalling the electric fence around the yard for those who have a pet to keep in the yard.      A well kept secret location nestled in the heart of Naples.  This location is within easy access to shopping, restaurants, hospitals, I-75, many churches, schools, and the Gulf of Mexico.
